  "summary": "Malicious code in mpesa-ui-components (npm)",
  "details": "During npm install (preinstall: node index.js), mpesa-ui-components collects hostname, username, homedir, cwd, DNS servers and the full package.json, then POSTs the JSON payload to hxxps://m-pesa[.]cleverapps[.]io/api/data/(hostname). Two HTTPS POSTs were observed. The package is two files (~812-byte index.js plus package.json) with zero UI components despite its name — a pure install-time host-fingerprint beacon.",
